                     <msItem n="4" xml:id="St_Johns_College_MS_203-item4">
                        <locus from="226r" to="238r">Fols. 226–38:</locus>
                        <rubric><supplied>M</supplied>oralium dogma philosophorum etc.</rubric>
                        <incipit>Quia fragilis res est memoria et rerum turbe non sufficit
                           necesse</incipit>
                        <explicit>sed rei magnitudo usum quoque exercitationemque
                           desiderat</explicit>
                        <incipit>aduersamini igitur vitia ut ait boecius in calce libri de
                           consolacione Virtutes colite et ad rectas spes</incipit>
                        <explicit>Indicta est et veritatis cum ante oculos uersemini Iudicis cunta
                           cernentis.</explicit>
                        <author key="person_29521941">GUILLAUME DE CONCHES</author>
                        <title key="work_5064"> Moralium dogma philosophorum</title>
                        <note><bibl>ed. John Holmberg, <title>Das Moralium dogma philosophorum des
                                 Guillaume de Conches</title> (Uppsala, 1929), 5–74</bibl>,
                           concluding with two sentences from <persName role="aut" key="person_100218964">BOETHIUS</persName>, <title key="work_1121">De
                              consolatione Philosophiae</title>, 5.p 6.47–8, <bibl>ed. Ludwig
                              Bieler, CC 94 (1984), 106.</bibl> This is the only formal text in this
                           section; the remainder presents a disorganized series of <title key="work_14583" type="desc">sermons</title> and <title key="work_14556" type="desc">sermon notes</title>, some in the hand
                           responsible for <locus from="224r" to="225r">fols. 224–5</locus>.</note>
                     </msItem>
